    <stitle>DT/DTI-466 A and B Series DT/DTI/DTA-466 C Diesel Engine Diagnostics (1993) - ENGINE DIAGNOSTIC TEST
        PROCEDURES - DT/DTI/DTA - 466 C SERIES DIESEL ENGINES - INJECTION PUMP STATIC TIMING [ENGINE STOPPED]
        DT/DTI/DTA-466 C Engines (With Robert Bosch "MW" or "A" Fuel Injection Pump)
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="proctype" graphiccount="4">
        <title>INJECTION PUMP STATIC TIMING [ENGINE STOPPED] DT/DTI/DTA-466 C Engines (With Robert Bosch "MW" or "A"
            Fuel Injection Pump)
        </title>
        <svcprocinfo>
            <table id="t4500610">
                <title>FROM FORM NO. CGED-365-*</title>
                <tgroup cols="6">
                    <colspec colname="1" colwidth="36p"/>
                    <colspec colname="2" colwidth="115p"/>
                    <colspec colname="3" colwidth="101p"/>
                    <colspec colname="4" colwidth="130p"/>
                    <colspec colname="5" colwidth="58p"/>
                    <colspec colname="6" colwidth="72p"/>
                    <spanspec namest="1" nameend="6" spanname="S1T6"/>
                    <spanspec namest="2" nameend="6" spanname="S2T6"/>
                    <tbody>
                        <row>
                            <entry colspan="6" spanname="S1T6">
                                <para>INJECTION PUMP STATIC TIMING [ENGINE STOPPED]</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry colname="1">
                                <para>9</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colspan="5" spanname="S2T6">
                                <para>A. TIMING VERIFICATION.</para>
                                <para>See Illustration - Reverse Side</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry colspan="6" spanname="S1T6">
                                <para>INSTRUMENT GUIDELINE DATA 1 st Check 2 nd Check</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry colname="1">
                                <para></para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="2">
                                <para>1. Visual Pointer Inspection</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="3">
                                <para></para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="4">
                                <para></para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="5">
                                <para></para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="6">
                                <para></para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                    </tbody>
                </tgroup>
            </table>
            <para>Refer to "Performance Data Guidelines" in this section.</para>
        </svcprocinfo>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Visual (Static) Timing Check</title>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Disconnect battery cables.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Disconnect accelerator cable from outer injection pump control lever.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove injection pump timing pointer plug and gasket from the left side of the pump
                    mounting adapter.
                </para>
                <specpara>
                    <warning>
                        <para>Shut-off must be in the no-fuel position before proceeding.</para>
                    </warning>
                </specpara>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Rotate the engine in the normal operating direction until the engine front cover timing
                    pointer is on the degree mark on the damper pulley for the particular application.
                    <emph type="bold">Refer to Figure
                        <hotlnk xrefid="ef4500638">6.38</hotlnk>
                    </emph>
                    and the Performance Data guidelines in this section.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Visually inspect the hub scribe line and timing pointer for alignment. If the scribe
                    line and timing pointer are aligned, the #1 piston is on the compression stroke.
                    <emph type="bold">Refer to Figures
                        <hotlnk xrefid="ef4500639">6.39</hotlnk>
                        and
                        <hotlnk xrefid="ef4500640">6.40</hotlnk>.
                    </emph>
                </para>
                <specpara>
                    <note>
                        <para>The above procedure establishes the accuracy of the previous timing and avoids the
                            necessity of removing the valve cover to establish the #1 compression stroke during
                            reassembly.
                        </para>
                    </note>
                </specpara>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Enter the observed pump to engine timing in the 1st check block of CGED-365-*.</para>
                <figure id="ef4500638" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="cg14737" filename="../figcg1/CG14737.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Figure 6.38 Static Pump to Engine Timing</caption>
                </figure>
                <para>
                    <emph type="bold">* - Form specified with latest revision.</emph>
                </para>
                <figure id="ef4500639" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="cg12470" filename="../figcg1/CG12470.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Figure 6.39 Timing Pointer and Mark [Robert Bosch "MW" shown]</caption>
                </figure>
                <figure id="ef4500640" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="cg14440" filename="../figcg1/CG14440.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Figure 6.40 Timing Pointer and Mark [Robert Bosch "A" Pump shown]</caption>
                </figure>
            </step1>
        </svcsubproc>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title></title>
            <para>If static timing is
                <emph type="bold">NOT</emph>
                within specifications, adjust pump to engine timing as follows:
            </para>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Rotate the engine crankshaft to the correct crankshaft position (static timing) as
                    specified in "Performance Data Guidelines," in this section.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the injection pump drive gear access cover. Discard the gasket.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Loosen injection pump drive gear bolts and washers to injection pump hub
                    <emph type="bold">(Figure
                        <hotlnk xrefid="ef4500641">6.41</hotlnk>)
                    </emph>
                    .
                </para>
                <figure id="ef4500641" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="cg10786" filename="../figcg1/CG10786.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Figure 6.41 Injection Pump Drive Gear Bolts</caption>
                </figure>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Rotate the pump drive hub as required for proper alignment of the timing pointer to the
                    drive hub mark.
                    <emph type="bold">Refer to Figure
                        <hotlnk xrefid="ef4500639">6.39</hotlnk>
                        and
                        <hotlnk xrefid="ef4500640">6.40</hotlnk>
                    </emph>
                    .
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Gently rotate the injection pump drive gear counterclockwise to remove the backlash.
                    Tighten the bolts to 35 lbf-ft. (47 N.m).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Visually confirm that the front cover timing pointer and crankshaft pulley degree mark
                    are aligned to the specified degree reading. Also confirm that the pump hub timing mark is aligned
                    with the timing pointer.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Recheck timing by rotating the engine crankshaft counterclockwise 90&#176;, and turn it
                    back to specified marks. Refer to "Performance Data Guidelines."
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Reinstall the access cover, using a new gasket.</para>
            </step1>
        </svcsubproc>
    </svcproc>
